@page
@model IndexModel

    <div class="container pt-lg-5 pb-lg-4">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-md-4"><u>Welcome To BookListRazor</u></h1>
        <div class="container text-justify">
            <p>A Simple ASP.NET Core Project that uses Razor pages. It demonstrates simple .Net Core CRUD operations as well as API calls using Controllers in Book Model. It validates the data field at both client-side and server-side.</p>
            <br />
            <p>
                <b><strong>Book(Normal Method)</strong></b> tab demonstrates CRUD operations that uses basic Razor page functionalities. The Delete operation is confirmed using alert message. <b><strong>Book(Enhanced Method)</strong></b> tab demonstrates CRUD operations that uses <i>API</i>  calls, retreiving table data in <i>JSON</i> format, table pagination using <i>dataTables</i>, alert message using <i>SweetAlert</i>, notification using <i>toastr</i> and <i>AJAX</i>. The <i>Create</i> and <i>Edit</i> operations share the same razor page.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
